<br>
1/ The zone is hardcapped at 72 people<br>
<br>
2/ A large portion of the mobs require a) 72 people, or b) perfect class composition.<br>
<br>
You are left with a few options: <br>
Do you over-recruit, and tell people &quot;Sorry dude, you can't raid tonight -- we're at the 72 limit.&quot; <br>
Or, do you <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>recruit</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> players who can be relied upon to be online 90% of the time, and are of a class that can benefit your raid party.<br>
<br>
Heaven and Earth chose the latter.<br>
<br>
Obviously (as Vindiinya stated) they are having issues with a few recruits, who they recruited with poor raid times. There is NO point in keeping these people onboard; so they are cutting them loose and filling their place with somebody else.<br>
<br>
They are almost completely reflagged, so they are just taking onboard a few people to replace the people they cut; before they kill the Elemental gods. If you think, for ONE second, they are having issues with not having enough recruits, you are truly kidding yourself. Hell, I could roll off at least 10 TWC people who have/are applying. At least.<br>
