<br>
Thats a correct statement.  Unfortunatly the more people you have the less DKP is distributed per person per raid.  Which sucks pretty much all the way around.<br>
<br>
&quot;You can't expect someone to wait around for an unknown amount of time till recruitment is reopened.&quot;<br>
<br>
Sure you can.  Happens all the time.  Well, sure they can.  Maybe you can't.<br>
<br>
&quot;Odds are they will go elsewhere.&quot;<br>
<br>
And still apply to HnE next time they take apps.  If they want in now chances are they will want in later.  I'm not saying there are'nt plenty of people who don't want in but those people would'nt apply in the first place.<br>
<br>
&quot;If you miss out on a great recruit because you closed recruiting, that's the system's fault.&quot;<br>
<br>
I guess you could say that.  If you don't have room when they are available you don't have room.  Being in the right place at the right time(or not being) is part of life.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm not saying it's not a fine system to go by, mass recruiting every once in awhile, but it does have that flaw&quot;<br>
<br>
Every system has that flaw.  The fact is if you recruited all the time there would be a steady stream of people all the time.  You could either bloat the guild and zerg everything.  Or you could just drop the bottom player from each class when someone better came along.  Both those options suck for obvious reasons.<br>
<br>
&quot;Actually, everything you posted concerns me.&quot;<br>
<br>
Cmon.  Lets be realistic.  Your just being a dick today.<br>
<br>
&quot;When we are in competing guilds&quot;<br>
<br>
TWC and HnE have'nt been competing guilds since the mass exodus of quality players you had left a couple years ago to join with HnE.  I don't know enough about TWC to know what caused it but HnE was no superpower at the time but TWC was struggling due to poor leadership and inactivity.<br>
<br>
&quot;You only recruit the unguilded people, right?&quot;<br>
<br>
Oh and you do?  No one &quot;only&quot; recruits unguilded people.<br>
<br>
&quot;You know what the biggest HnE complaint was during all that time? They were upset because OOP was targeting their clerics for recruitment, promising them loot if they applied, etc etc. I find it quite humorous that a guild which used to complain about another guild secretly recruiting their members now engages in that same practice.&quot;<br>
<br>
Recruiting someone means going to them and making an offer.  Someone coming to you and applying is not recruiting.  Furthermore theres no offer of leet lewt or special favors.  HnE is DKP.  You start at 0 and end at whatever you earn.  You should have figured out through your own game experience that not everything everyone says on the internet is true.  Just because some gimp fed you a story about how you better treat them better because HnE is trying to Lure their leet skills away with phat lewts doesnt mean its true.<br>
<br>
&quot;That is the reason behind you always mentioning that HnE applications are confidential.&quot;<br>
<br>
That has nothing to do with recruiting people.  It has to do with people feeling comfortable putting in their app knowing they may very well be turned down.  It wouldnt even relate to someone who was being &quot;recruited&quot; since there would seemingly be no chance they would be turned away if they were already being offered some sweet deal.  I mean at least thin this shit out.  That does'nt even make fucking sense genious.<br>
<br>
&quot;Every other major guild on the server has kept from making their recruitment into some great spectacular event that it really isn't.&quot;<br>
<br>
Maybe is spectacular to you.  Its not meant to be spectacular its meant to be well known so you get the most apps and the best choice of applicants.  Its common sense.<br>
<br>
&quot;But I'll level with you, HnE's standards aren't exactly what they used to be.&quot;<br>
<br>
Hipocrit says what?<br>
